Readings : Audio, Video, Images

SUMMARY:

IMAGES:
  1. Images can be aligned both horizontally and vertically using CSS.
  2. With CSS, we can specify the dimension of the images.
  3. We can use the background image behind the box created by any element on a page.
  4. Background images can appear onbce or can be repeated across the background of the box.
  5. We can create image rollover effects by moving background position of an image.
  6. Image sprites can be created to re4duce the number of images the browser has to load.
  
 PRACTICAL INFORMATION:
  1.  Search Engine otimization helps user find our sites.
  2.  Analytics tools such as Gooogle Analytics gives us the number of traffice visiting our sites.
  3.  To host our pages, we need to obtain a domain name and web hosting.
  4.  FTP programs allow us to transfer files from our local computer to the web browser.
  
 Bookmark/skim:
  1. HTML5 instroduces new ,video> and ,audio> elements for adding video and audio to web pages, but these are only supported in latest browsers.
  2. Browsers that support the HTML5 elements do not all support the same video and audio formats, so we need to supply the files in differstn formats.
  
 
